      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "MELEYS (5) is in good hands. Wound up strongly to finish 1.1 lengths adrift, first-up over 1235m at Geelong. Has more to give and may be able to settle a bit closer today. Go close. ROYAL SWAY (6) was only beaten 0.8 lengths resuming from a spell over 1200m at Morphettville. Drove hard to just miss in a tight finish. That stacks right up, and she will finish hard as well. Feared. HEAVY IS THE HEAD (2) settled last in a 12-horse field and impressed at Pakenham first up, going down by just 1.4L. Just a run at Gellong following, but she will be fitter, and this is easier. Is still shy of her best, and the longer sprint will suit. Keep onside. SHINE TOGETHER (8) has been in the market both her starts and John Allen stays aboard. We can expect improvement from her.",
